00:52:21.790 --> 00:52:26.940
And be a woman that really
didn't do with any nonsense

00:52:26.940 --> 00:52:28.570
and hate to be interrupted
when she was reading,

00:52:28.570 --> 00:52:31.690
she promptly hold the
rat out of the pool

00:52:31.690 --> 00:52:36.850
and that was the end of that.

00:52:36.850 --> 00:52:40.210
So our panel is going
to talk about what works

00:52:40.210 --> 00:52:43.010
in reading promotion,
not the research.

00:52:43.010 --> 00:52:46.260
What works, what doesn't
work, and opportunities

00:52:46.260 --> 00:52:51.310
in this current time, in
2018 to promote reading.

00:52:51.310 --> 00:52:55.550
And just very briefly, what
I'm going to say is, of course,

00:52:55.550 --> 00:52:59.230
what I've seen is that
it's absolutely critical

00:52:59.230 --> 00:53:04.220
to have a strong charismatic
leader who leads the charge

00:53:04.220 --> 00:53:07.090
that urges people to read.

00:53:07.090 --> 00:53:10.130
Now, that doesn't mean it has

00:53:10.130 --> 00:53:14.080
to be a serious eat your
piece kind of message.

00:53:14.080 --> 00:53:16.620
You have to illustrate
why reading is fun,

00:53:16.620 --> 00:53:20.910
why it's necessary to do
your job, why it's necessary

00:53:20.910 --> 00:53:23.790
to perform in the democracy,

00:53:23.790 --> 00:53:25.730
someone whose voice
can be heard.

00:53:25.730 --> 00:53:29.920
And frankly, in this world
in which we're living,

00:53:29.920 --> 00:53:33.710
I have seen that we really need

00:53:33.710 --> 00:53:37.220
to have leaders,
cultural leaders.

00:53:37.220 --> 00:53:41.010
Culture such it is but the
current culture who stand up

00:53:41.010 --> 00:53:46.190
and talk about why
read, why do they read.

00:53:46.190 --> 00:53:50.630
And I'm talking about rock
stars, baseball players,

00:53:50.630 --> 00:53:54.140
basketball players,
football players,

00:53:54.140 --> 00:53:59.640
people that will encourage
today's-- not us, we read,

00:53:59.640 --> 00:54:04.250
people that will encourage
today's youth to read.

00:54:04.250 --> 00:54:07.670
Years ago, there was a very
effective campaign called Get

00:54:07.670 --> 00:54:08.970
Caught Reading.

00:54:08.970 --> 00:54:11.310
I don't know if any of you
are old enough to remember it.

00:54:11.310 --> 00:54:14.800
I'm 73 although I know
I look much younger.

00:54:14.800 --> 00:54:19.590
And there were posters all over
the country of movie stars,

00:54:19.590 --> 00:54:21.880
television stars, everybody.

00:54:21.880 --> 00:54:25.430
And this really funny posters
saying get caught reading

00:54:25.430 --> 00:54:27.830
and there would be a book.

00:54:27.830 --> 00:54:29.840
Can't we have something
like that today

00:54:29.840 --> 00:54:32.730
that says get caught reading?

00:54:32.730 --> 00:54:35.860
And let me tell you why I
read or why I love books

00:54:35.860 --> 00:54:39.270
and have a LeBron
James who, by the way,

00:54:39.270 --> 00:54:40.900
is a big literacy supporter.

00:54:40.900 --> 00:54:44.130
Talk about why he loves book.

00:54:44.130 --> 00:54:45.430
I'm talking about posters.

00:54:45.430 --> 00:54:49.200
I'm talking about
billboards, that sort of thing.

00:54:49.200 --> 00:54:53.670
And yes, we do need books to
be widely and easily available.

00:54:53.670 --> 00:54:57.260
Another program I'm on currently
on the board of is Reach Out

00:54:57.260 --> 00:54:59.830
and Read, which is a
pediatric literacy program.

00:54:59.830 --> 00:55:01.630
And yes--

00:55:01.630 --> 00:55:05.670
[ Applause ]

00:55:05.670 --> 00:55:10.730
And this again is outside
the box, outside the schools,

00:55:10.730 --> 00:55:14.940
outside the traditional places
where books are given out.

00:55:14.940 --> 00:55:18.080
Doctors give books
every well-baby visit

00:55:18.080 --> 00:55:21.910
from the time the child is
born up to five years of age

00:55:21.910 --> 00:55:25.630
with instruction to the
parent on how to read,

00:55:25.630 --> 00:55:28.810
even if the parent
isn't a brilliant reader

00:55:28.810 --> 00:55:31.220
to the child, the interaction.

00:55:31.220 --> 00:55:37.300
And very often you
find that parents,

00:55:37.300 --> 00:55:41.090
particularly parents
whom I come from,

00:55:41.090 --> 00:55:42.420
impoverished backgrounds will be

00:55:42.420 --> 00:55:45.790
in an impoverished situation
don't understand how important

00:55:45.790 --> 00:55:48.240
it is for them to be
reading to their children.

00:55:48.240 --> 00:55:51.490
They understand very fast
once they get that first book

00:55:51.490 --> 00:55:53.800
and they develop their
own reading habits

00:55:53.800 --> 00:55:57.030
and it increases the bond
between parent and child.

00:55:57.030 --> 00:55:59.870
So yes, let's make books
available but not just

00:55:59.870 --> 00:56:05.280
in all the usual places, let's
reach out and be where families.

00:56:05.280 --> 00:56:08.500
Families, by the way,
children go home from school,

00:56:08.500 --> 00:56:10.160
their parents are in the house.

00:56:10.160 --> 00:56:11.890
They're not living
in orphanages.

00:56:11.890 --> 00:56:14.240
So if we just look at fixing
the schools and don't look

