Family Reading Circles.

00:58:49.470 --> 00:58:53.450
And Family Reading Circles
actually started with a request

00:58:53.450 --> 00:58:56.320
from the Maryland
Humanities Council that wanted

00:58:56.320 --> 00:59:00.740
to do a family reading program.

00:59:00.740 --> 00:59:04.880
Kind of designed after what
was a big deal in those days,

00:59:04.880 --> 00:59:06.640
which was Oprah's book club.

00:59:06.640 --> 00:59:09.320
And what it meant was that
you were bringing books

00:59:09.320 --> 00:59:11.460
and food together with families.

00:59:11.460 --> 00:59:15.730
And as you can see, this young
lady has abandoned her dinner

00:59:15.730 --> 00:59:18.830
in order to examine
the books that we are--

00:59:18.830 --> 00:59:20.510
that they were going
to take home.

00:59:20.510 --> 00:59:25.290
The Family Reading Circle
program is a six weeks program

00:59:25.290 --> 00:59:28.670
that we do in branches,
that we do in schools,

00:59:28.670 --> 00:59:30.460
after-school programs.

00:59:30.460 --> 00:59:34.460
We've even done this program
in transitional housing.

00:59:34.460 --> 00:59:38.120
We have done this program
in community centers.

00:59:38.120 --> 00:59:41.350
And so, it's been in
a variety of places.

00:59:41.350 --> 00:59:43.750
But the main idea
of the program is

00:59:43.750 --> 00:59:48.640
that families come together
once a week for six weeks.

00:59:48.640 --> 00:59:53.060
Each week, they get two
high-quality picture books.

00:59:53.060 --> 00:59:57.930
We read the books aloud
together and discussed them.

00:59:57.930 --> 01:00:01.980
We choose books that have
wonderful family themes,

01:00:01.980 --> 01:00:04.230
but we also choose books
that are a lot of fun,

01:00:04.230 --> 01:00:09.150
have a lot of wordplay, so
that we not only tell people

01:00:09.150 --> 01:00:11.020
that it can be fun
to enjoy reading.

01:00:11.020 --> 01:00:12.470
We model it.

01:00:12.470 --> 01:00:13.770
One of the great things

01:00:13.770 --> 01:00:18.820
about this program is how many
parents didn't have these kinds

01:00:18.820 --> 01:00:20.480
of books for themselves.

01:00:20.480 --> 01:00:22.540
And how much joy and
delight they take

01:00:22.540 --> 01:00:28.400
in finding these books.

01:00:28.400 --> 01:00:30.280
You can see one of the
things that we love

01:00:30.280 --> 01:00:32.890
about this program
is it attracts dads,

01:00:32.890 --> 01:00:35.060
not just moms but attracts dads.

01:00:35.060 --> 01:00:39.540
Well, we also encourage grand
mom, we encourage all kinds

01:00:39.540 --> 01:00:40.990
of folks to participate.

01:00:40.990 --> 01:00:43.900
We-- One big hallmark
of the program is

01:00:43.900 --> 01:00:48.400
to celebrate the parents, we
give the trophy to the parents,

01:00:48.400 --> 01:00:52.900
we recognize that what it takes
for a parent to come after work

01:00:52.900 --> 01:00:56.240
for six weeks to be a
part of a reading program

01:00:56.240 --> 01:01:00.780
as the big sacrifice and we
honor them for doing that.

01:01:02.590 --> 01:01:06.630
There's a great deal of
interaction between the families

01:01:06.630 --> 01:01:09.420
and the children when
they come to the program.

01:01:09.420 --> 01:01:14.630
They really enjoy being a part
of that particular activity.

01:01:28.750 --> 01:01:31.880
In addition to giving
trophies to the parents,

01:01:31.880 --> 01:01:34.210
every family gets a certificate,

01:01:34.210 --> 01:01:37.610
one of the slides I don't
have here is at the end

01:01:37.610 --> 01:01:42.280
of the program we take a
picture of the family together

01:01:42.280 --> 01:01:45.880
and they are placed in a
frame called family readers.

01:01:45.880 --> 01:01:48.180
So that's one of the
things that they take away

01:01:48.180 --> 01:01:51.500
that they will have to remind
them of this great opportunity

01:01:51.500 --> 01:01:54.720
and great experience
they had together.

01:01:54.720 --> 01:01:59.520
One of the things that we do
when we have author visits

01:01:59.520 --> 01:02:02.190
at the Pratt library
is that we make sure

01:02:02.190 --> 01:02:04.740
that the students
go home with books.

01:02:04.740 --> 01:02:07.920
As we heard from
the previous panel,

01:02:07.920 --> 01:02:10.050
the most important
thing is to have books

01:02:10.050 --> 01:02:11.780
and to have access to books.

01:02:11.780 --> 01:02:14.150
And we used to get
questions about that,

01:02:14.150 --> 01:02:15.450
why are you giving people books?

01:02:15.450 --> 01:02:18.140
You should just want to
give them a library card.

01:02:18.140 --> 01:02:20.470
One of the things that we
know and one of the things

01:02:20.470 --> 01:02:22.560
that I know from being
a voracious reader

01:02:22.560 --> 01:02:24.500
and a voracious library
reader is

01:02:24.500 --> 01:02:27.130
that when you become a
community of readers or part

01:02:27.130 --> 01:02:30.650
of the community of readers you
buy books, you borrow books,

01:02:30.650 --> 01:02:33.250
you have books, books
are all around you.

01:02:33.250 --> 01:02:38.360
So we want to make sure that we
encourage kids by having books

01:02:38.360 --> 01:02:41.350
that they take can
take home themselves.

01:02:41.350 --> 01:02:46.070
This particular visit was
with authors, Zetta Elliot.

01:02:46.070 --> 01:02:49.920
She came to Baltimore, she
did a number of programs

01:02:49.920 --> 01:02:54.170
